00:47:16,909 --> 00:47:20,277
People used to
openly worship here.

769
00:47:23,049 --> 00:47:25,816
A belief system
based entirely upon faith.

770
00:47:30,256 --> 00:47:32,923
Medorin told you
we can't help you.

771
00:47:32,925 --> 00:47:35,726
- (DOOR OPENS)
- (FOOTSTEPS APPROACH)

772
00:47:37,263 --> 00:47:39,396
So why are you here?

773
00:47:43,402 --> 00:47:46,804
I understand
why you don't trust me.

774
00:47:49,008 --> 00:47:51,575
I thought people like you
were bad.

775
00:47:52,845 --> 00:47:54,845
I thought you were broken.

776
00:47:55,581 --> 00:47:58,349
Searching for a truth
that doesn't exist.

777
00:47:58,351 --> 00:48:00,818
I thought Logos was doing
the same.

778
00:48:03,623 --> 00:48:05,890
It all seemed wrong.

779
00:48:09,028 --> 00:48:12,696
I came face to face with
what scared me the most.

780
00:48:12,698 --> 00:48:14,165
Believing in something

781
00:48:14,167 --> 00:48:17,501
so different to
the world I've known.

782
00:48:20,606 --> 00:48:24,875
I felt that way because that's
how the Pilot wanted me to feel.

783
00:48:28,581 --> 00:48:31,482
After I stopped taking
my Maintenance...

784
00:48:32,351 --> 00:48:35,386
..I realised
you're far from broken.

785
00:48:36,589 --> 00:48:39,356
And the truth you're
searching for does exist.

786
00:48:39,358 --> 00:48:41,659
You stopped taking
your Maintenance?

787
00:48:43,129 --> 00:48:44,862
Completely.

788
00:48:46,265 --> 00:48:48,732
You still haven't answered
my question.

789
00:48:51,938 --> 00:48:54,004
I found Logos.

790
00:48:54,006 --> 00:48:56,540
He's in Daden.

791
00:48:56,542 --> 00:48:59,510
His mind has been wiped
and he needs to be restored.

792
00:48:59,512 --> 00:49:03,314
We need to save him
and you're going to help me.

793
00:49:04,584 --> 00:49:06,850
PILOT'S DAUGHTER: Why won't you
tell me the real reason

794
00:49:06,852 --> 00:49:08,886
Helias left you and the machine?

795
00:49:08,888 --> 00:49:11,388
THE PILOT: He was jealous.

796
00:49:11,390 --> 00:49:13,991
You know about mortal jealousy.

797
00:49:13,993 --> 00:49:16,327
For him to turn so quickly
on you,

798
00:49:16,329 --> 00:49:18,262
he must have had a reason.

799
00:49:19,031 --> 00:49:21,332
It was nothing of the sort.

800
00:49:27,306 --> 00:49:30,241
It's Logos. He's gone.

801
00:49:30,243 --> 00:49:33,644
(TENSE MUSIC)

802
00:49:36,983 --> 00:49:39,383
Gone?

803
00:49:40,553 --> 00:49:42,519
What do you mean gone?
Gone where?

804
00:49:54,100 --> 00:49:56,033
He didn't report to his office.

805
00:49:56,035 --> 00:49:58,736
His data is gone too.

806
00:49:58,738 --> 00:50:02,373
Akae must have downloaded it
directly.

807
00:50:06,779 --> 00:50:08,612
(SCANNER TRILLS)

808
00:50:10,783 --> 00:50:12,750
Find them!

809
00:50:17,523 --> 00:50:21,425
Everything's going to be OK.
I promise.

810
00:50:22,528 --> 00:50:25,663
I know what it's like to feel
really unsure about something.

811
00:50:26,899 --> 00:50:28,632
What do you mean?

812
00:50:30,102 --> 00:50:32,803
I grew up in a world
that was perfect.

813
00:50:32,805 --> 00:50:35,039
Made for me by the Pilot.

814
00:50:35,041 --> 00:50:36,774
For all of us.

815
00:50:39,378 --> 00:50:41,545
That's what I thought at least.

816
00:50:41,547 --> 00:50:45,649
But there were these...
questions,

817
00:50:45,651 --> 00:50:48,652
these thoughts I kept having.

818
00:50:48,654 --> 00:50:51,555
Like maybe there was
something more

819
00:50:51,557 --> 00:50:53,924
underneath all the perfection.

820
00:50:55,261 --> 00:50:57,928
But I was wrong
for having those thoughts.

821
00:50:57,930 --> 00:51:00,698
I was wrong to question
the life I was given.

822
00:51:01,634 --> 00:51:04,401
But those same questions
are coming back

823
00:51:04,403 --> 00:51:08,672
and it's seemingly impossible
to push them away.

824
00:51:11,977 --> 00:51:14,545
Why are you saying this?

825
00:51:16,916 --> 00:51:19,016
Because you're not going to
remember any of it

826
00:51:19,018 --> 00:51:20,384
in a few minutes.

827
00:51:20,386 --> 00:51:22,619
We're going to bring you back.

828
00:51:25,491 --> 00:51:27,224
There was nothing in Akae's data

829
00:51:27,226 --> 00:51:29,059
that indicated
this should've happened.

830
00:51:29,061 --> 00:51:32,329
Perhaps her data was inaccurate.

831
00:51:32,331 --> 00:51:34,631
Her scan showed normal levels
of Maintenance.

832
00:51:34,633 --> 00:51:38,302
I trusted you. I shouldn't have.

833
00:51:38,304 --> 00:51:40,738
(TENSE MUSIC INTENSIFIES)

834
00:51:40,740 --> 00:51:42,873
AKAE: Logos?

835
00:51:44,577 --> 00:51:46,043
Logos?

836
00:51:48,013 --> 00:51:49,613
Logos!

837
00:51:52,284 --> 00:51:54,418
It was surreal -

838
00:51:54,420 --> 00:51:58,088
you were you but you weren't.

839
00:52:00,326 --> 00:52:02,693
You had no idea who I was.

840
00:52:03,429 --> 00:52:05,696
No idea who you were.

841
00:52:08,134 --> 00:52:09,900
I'm glad you're back.

842
00:52:10,836 --> 00:52:12,836
I'm glad to be back.

843
00:52:17,176 --> 00:52:18,876
(PULSING MUSIC)

844
00:52:18,878 --> 00:52:20,310
Sonitas has a plan -

845
00:52:20,312 --> 00:52:22,112
a way to show the world
who we are.

846
00:52:22,114 --> 00:52:25,416
The Pilot's global address will
be broadcast in just a few days.

847
00:52:25,418 --> 00:52:26,950
I've found a way
to hack into it.

848
00:52:26,952 --> 00:52:30,053
This will allow us to replace
the Pilot's feed with our own.

849
00:52:30,055 --> 00:52:32,756
Of course, before we do this,
we need to alter the Maintenance

850
00:52:32,758 --> 00:52:34,491
to make sure
our message is heard.

851
00:52:34,493 --> 00:52:37,795
Which didn't go so well
last time.

852
00:52:40,366 --> 00:52:42,166
I have a plan.

853
00:52:43,769 --> 00:52:45,369
And here is a brief explanation

854
00:52:45,371 --> 00:52:48,305
about how our colony began
exactly 200 years ago.

855
00:52:48,307 --> 00:52:50,307
- That was really good.
- OK, now you try.

856
00:52:50,309 --> 00:52:53,510
And here is a brief explanation
about how our colony began...

857
00:52:55,848 --> 00:52:58,649
I can't talk long
but I need your help.

858
00:53:03,923 --> 00:53:07,124
(FOREBODING MUSIC)

859
00:53:22,274 --> 00:53:23,707
Thank you.

860
00:53:23,709 --> 00:53:26,376
I promise it'll make sense
why I've asked you to do this.

861
00:53:26,378 --> 00:53:29,179
- (DOOR UNLOCKS)
- We trust you, Akae.

862
00:53:34,186 --> 00:53:36,520
(TICKING AND BLEEPING)

863
00:53:49,335 --> 00:53:51,235
Why don't you do the honours?

864
00:53:51,237 --> 00:53:54,037
(TENSE MUSIC)

865
00:54:16,395 --> 00:54:18,362
(WHIRRS AND HISSES)

866
00:54:18,364 --> 00:54:20,898
(STATIC AND BUZZING)

867
00:54:22,101 --> 00:54:23,634
(NOISES STOP)

868
00:54:26,872 --> 00:54:28,038
(POWERS UP)

869
00:54:28,974 --> 00:54:31,174
(CHUCKLES)

870
00:54:31,176 --> 00:54:33,710
It works. Let's go.

871
00:54:37,950 --> 00:54:41,118
(BIRDSONG)

872
00:54:42,421 --> 00:54:44,187
(METALLIC CLINK)

873
00:54:53,299 --> 00:54:55,132
MEDORIN: I just heard
from Masim.

874
00:54:55,134 --> 00:54:57,367
They should be here
the day after tomorrow.

875
00:54:57,369 --> 00:54:59,603
- Have they heard from Gergot?
- Not yet.

876
00:54:59,605 --> 00:55:02,339
I'm sure he's just out
gathering supplies.

877
00:55:02,341 --> 00:55:04,708
(INSECTS CHIRP)

878
00:55:14,954 --> 00:55:18,922
LOGOS: <i>"In anguish, I apprehend
myself at once as totally free</i>

879
00:55:18,924 --> 00:55:21,658
<i>"and as not being able to derive
the meaning of the world</i>

880
00:55:21,660 --> 00:55:24,595
<i>"except as coming from myself.</i>

881
00:55:24,597 --> 00:55:26,563
<i>"The recruit who reports
for active duty</i>

882
00:55:26,565 --> 00:55:27,931
<i>"at the beginning of the war</i>

883
00:55:27,933 --> 00:55:31,101
<i>"can in some instances
be afraid of death,</i>

884
00:55:31,103 --> 00:55:35,005
<i>"but more often
he is afraid of being afraid."</i>

885
00:55:43,148 --> 00:55:44,881
I'm sorry. I...

886
00:55:49,121 --> 00:55:51,021
Is it Gergot?

887
00:55:54,727 --> 00:55:57,661
Taken by the watchers
and wiped clean.

888
00:55:59,965 --> 00:56:02,265
I'm sorry.

889
00:56:02,267 --> 00:56:04,034
Me too.

890
00:56:05,237 --> 00:56:11,208
You know, sometimes I wonder if
the Pilot didn't have it right,

891
00:56:11,210 --> 00:56:13,410
with the pain of loss.

892
00:56:16,015 --> 00:56:17,514
We can find him.

893
00:56:17,516 --> 00:56:19,049
Restore him, like I was.

894
00:56:19,051 --> 00:56:22,653
With the Pilot aware of us
and what we've been up to...

895
00:56:23,522 --> 00:56:25,255
..I hope so.

896
00:56:28,661 --> 00:56:31,862
I'll be just across the way
if you need anything.

897
00:56:36,669 --> 00:56:38,402
Thank you, Logos.

898
00:56:43,509 --> 00:56:46,076
I couldn't risk
leaving it behind.

899
00:56:46,078 --> 00:56:48,945
(MYSTERIOUS MUSIC)

900
00:57:03,762 --> 00:57:05,862
MASIM: The altered Maintenance
is being distributed.

901
00:57:05,864 --> 00:57:08,832
Tomorrow an entire society
will be waking up

902
00:57:08,834 --> 00:57:10,801
with a new lens on the world.

903
00:57:10,803 --> 00:57:13,170
Our time to speak out is here.

904
00:57:13,172 --> 00:57:14,771
Once we've breached
the Pilot's address,

905
00:57:14,773 --> 00:57:18,842
our faces, our beliefs
will be made known to the world.

906
00:57:18,844 --> 00:57:21,812
We won't get another chance.
This is it.

907
00:57:21,814 --> 00:57:24,414
We need to make sure our voices
are heard and heard well.

908
00:57:24,416 --> 00:57:26,149
What if it worked?

909
00:57:27,653 --> 00:57:29,619
What do you mean?

910
00:57:29,621 --> 00:57:31,521
The Code Diffuser.
What if it worked?

911
00:57:31,523 --> 00:57:34,491
It's a prototype.

912
00:57:34,493 --> 00:57:35,926
Without Helias's mind data,

913
00:57:35,928 --> 00:57:38,595
we have no idea of knowing
how effective it would be.

914
00:57:38,597 --> 00:57:40,897
But if it were to work on me?

915
00:57:41,834 --> 00:57:45,435
Then you'd be the first
mortal citizen on this planet

916
00:57:45,437 --> 00:57:47,504
in over a century.

917
00:58:14,266 --> 00:58:16,166
(SIGHS)

918
00:58:23,575 --> 00:58:25,776
Hey.

919
00:58:28,147 --> 00:58:30,180
Did you mean it?

920
00:58:31,150 --> 00:58:32,949
Yeah.

921
00:58:37,623 --> 00:58:39,089
Akae, I...

922
00:58:39,091 --> 00:58:40,824
It's fine.

923
00:58:41,794 --> 00:58:43,960
If you want to die,

924
00:58:43,962 --> 00:58:46,229
it's your prerogative.

925
00:58:48,033 --> 00:58:50,233
It's not that I want to die.

926
00:58:51,336 --> 00:58:52,736
No?

927
00:58:52,738 --> 00:58:54,471
Then what is it?

928
00:58:55,507 --> 00:58:58,074
I want to live.

929
00:58:59,611 --> 00:59:02,813
I want to not know
what day is my last.

930
00:59:02,815 --> 00:59:06,550
To make decisions
with consequences.

931
00:59:08,453 --> 00:59:10,954
Real consequences.

932
00:59:13,225 --> 00:59:18,862
I want to know what it's like
to feel everything.

933
00:59:22,601 --> 00:59:25,302
And I can't do that like this.

934
00:59:28,140 --> 00:59:32,142
I can't do that if I know
that I'm going to live forever.

935
00:59:50,495 --> 00:59:52,195
(PANTS)

936
00:59:55,601 --> 00:59:58,368
(ZAPPING AND WHIRRING)

937
00:59:58,370 --> 01:00:02,272
(AKAE'S VOICE ECHOES)
Logos! Wake up!

938
01:00:02,274 --> 01:00:05,876
(CLEARLY)
Logos, wake up. Wake up!

939
01:00:05,878 --> 01:00:09,045
Medorin! Medorin!

940
01:00:09,047 --> 01:00:11,648
What's wrong with him?

941
01:00:11,650 --> 01:00:13,450
He used the diffuser.

942
01:00:13,452 --> 01:00:15,518
(WHISPERS) Logos.

943
01:00:15,520 --> 01:00:16,853
What can I do?

944
01:00:16,855 --> 01:00:19,589
If we don't stabilise him,
we might lose him.

945
01:00:19,591 --> 01:00:21,224
AKAE: Logos.

946
01:00:21,226 --> 01:00:23,793
Logos, wake up.

947
01:00:23,795 --> 01:00:25,929
Do something, please.

948
01:00:28,901 --> 01:00:32,636
(WHISPERS) Logos.
Wake up. Listen to me.

949
01:00:32,638 --> 01:00:34,638
- Listen.
- (TENSE MUSIC)

950
01:00:37,442 --> 01:00:39,910
(BIRDS CHIRP AND SQUAWK)

951
01:01:01,333 --> 01:01:04,567
His body's still in shock
but he's stable.

952
01:01:05,504 --> 01:01:06,670
He'll need a few days

953
01:01:06,672 --> 01:01:08,972
before he can handle
another change to his genome.

954
01:01:08,974 --> 01:01:12,042
Then we can attempt at
reapplying the Code.

955
01:01:17,082 --> 01:01:19,416
His data was never scanned
and saved,

956
01:01:19,418 --> 01:01:24,154
so who knows if his memories
remain intact.

957
01:01:25,590 --> 01:01:27,557
This is uncharted territory.

958
01:01:27,559 --> 01:01:30,460
(WISTFUL MUSIC)

959
01:01:53,418 --> 01:01:55,618
(INSECTS CHIRP)

960
01:02:34,459 --> 01:02:35,658
Logos.

961
01:02:45,704 --> 01:02:47,637
He's stable.

962
01:02:50,142 --> 01:02:52,342
I'll let you two talk.

963
01:02:52,344 --> 01:02:54,110
Hey.

964
01:02:56,481 --> 01:02:57,914
I'm sorry.

965
01:02:57,916 --> 01:02:59,682
I didn't mean to hurt you.

966
01:02:59,684 --> 01:03:01,051
It's OK.

967
01:03:01,053 --> 01:03:03,353
How do you feel?

968
01:03:03,355 --> 01:03:05,388
Different.

969
01:03:08,860 --> 01:03:11,194
Different how?

970
01:03:13,131 --> 01:03:15,832
Everything is just...

971
01:03:16,868 --> 01:03:18,668
..clear.

972
01:03:19,905 --> 01:03:22,105
Do you like what you see?

973
01:03:23,608 --> 01:03:25,408
I do.

974
01:03:33,485 --> 01:03:35,251
Me too.

975
01:03:38,056 --> 01:03:40,323
At first, I...

976
01:03:41,593 --> 01:03:44,194
..I came to Daden,

977
01:03:44,196 --> 01:03:47,697
I had to get through
to you and...

978
01:03:47,699 --> 01:03:49,299
And what?

979
01:03:52,504 --> 01:03:54,270
I kissed you.

980
01:03:55,907 --> 01:03:58,274
I don't know why.

981
01:03:58,276 --> 01:04:01,377
A feeling just came over me.

982
01:04:03,415 --> 01:04:06,216
A feeling
I've never felt before.

983
01:04:08,753 --> 01:04:10,620
I just thought you should know.

984
01:04:12,824 --> 01:04:15,258
I'm glad you told me.

985
01:04:16,094 --> 01:04:17,760
(LOGOS CHUCKLES)

986
01:04:35,647 --> 01:04:37,680
Sonitas is almost in.

987
01:04:42,120 --> 01:04:44,721
Are you sure
you want to do this?

988
01:04:45,690 --> 01:04:48,791
Because once you do,

989
01:04:48,793 --> 01:04:51,060
once you put yourself out there,

990
01:04:51,062 --> 01:04:53,763
explaining what you've done,

991
01:04:53,765 --> 01:04:55,498
there's no going back.

992
01:04:56,334 --> 01:04:59,135
And there's no telling
what could happen.

993
01:04:59,137 --> 01:05:01,204
I have to.

994
01:05:05,477 --> 01:05:07,377
Then I'll be right by your side.

995
01:05:14,119 --> 01:05:16,553
<i>Citizens.</i>

996
01:05:16,555 --> 01:05:18,621
<i>It is with gratitude
and humility</i>

997
01:05:18,623 --> 01:05:20,623
<i>that I come to you today
to talk,</i>

998
01:05:20,625 --> 01:05:23,326
<i>as we always do,
about our society.</i>

999
01:05:24,196 --> 01:05:27,564
(DRAMATIC MUSIC)

1000
01:05:27,566 --> 01:05:30,600
<i>I know you were expecting to be
addressed by the Pilot.</i>

1001
01:05:31,703 --> 01:05:35,939
<i>But please, hear me out.</i>

1002
01:05:37,642 --> 01:05:39,375
My name is Logos.

1003
01:05:39,377 --> 01:05:43,646
<i>I've been a citizen living
amongst you my entire life.</i>

1004
01:05:43,648 --> 01:05:45,081
What's going on?!

1005
01:05:45,083 --> 01:05:47,383
LOGOS: <i>And recently,
I've wondered</i>

1006
01:05:47,385 --> 01:05:50,186
<i>what my purpose was
on this planet.</i>

1007
01:05:50,188 --> 01:05:53,289
<i>I started asking myself
questions,</i>

1008
01:05:53,291 --> 01:05:56,326
<i>questions about how we live.</i>

1009
01:05:56,328 --> 01:05:59,462
<i>And I started to find answers.</i>

1010
01:06:00,398 --> 01:06:03,266
I am no longer
under control of the Pilot.

1011
01:06:03,268 --> 01:06:06,336
I am no longer imprisoned
by the Code.

1012
01:06:06,338 --> 01:06:08,271
<i>I've diffused it.</i>

1013
01:06:08,273 --> 01:06:10,573
- <i>Freed myself from its reins.</i>
- (BANGS TABLE)

1014
01:06:10,575 --> 01:06:16,012
<i>The Pilot created you to be
who he wants you to be,</i>

1015
01:06:16,014 --> 01:06:18,648
<i>to live as he wants you to live.</i>

1016
01:06:18,650 --> 01:06:20,550
Now that my eyes
have been opened,

1017
01:06:20,552 --> 01:06:24,654
I realised how much darkness
has been hiding underneath.

1018
01:06:25,890 --> 01:06:28,157
<i>The Pilot made you...</i>

1019
01:06:28,159 --> 01:06:32,695
<i>..designed you to be hollow...</i>

1020
01:06:33,865 --> 01:06:35,598
<i>..to be empty inside,</i>

1021
01:06:35,600 --> 01:06:40,169
to never see the beauty of life
that I now see.

1022
01:06:40,171 --> 01:06:42,372
Listen to me, all of you!

1023
01:06:42,374 --> 01:06:46,175
I am mortal and I am alive!

1024
01:06:46,177 --> 01:06:48,511
